@page "/about"
@attribute [Authorize]
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>About · Countdown to August 5th</PageTitle>

<div class="about-page">

    <!-- Back -->
    <a href="/" class="about-back">← Back</a>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="about-hero">
        <div class="about-hero-eyebrow">August 5th, 2026</div>
        <h1 class="about-hero-title">Two people.<br/>One day.</h1>
        <p class="about-hero-sub">
            Somewhere between right now and August 5th, 2026, two people who really
            want to see each other will finally get to start something amazing together — in person.
            This site exists to count every single day, hour, minute, and second until that moment.
        </p>
        <div class="about-heart-row">
            <span class="about-heart">♡</span>
            <span class="about-heart">♡</span>
            <span class="about-heart">♡</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Features -->
    <div class="about-section-label">What this site does</div>

    <div class="about-features">

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">🎨</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">A new painting every day</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    Every morning at midnight, an AI finds a holiday being celebrated somewhere
                    in the world and commissions a brand-new oil painting in the style of Bob Ross —
                    generated by Flux 2 Pro, one of the most advanced image models on the planet.
                    No two days ever look the same.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">🎬</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">The painting comes alive</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    After each painting is generated, it's passed to Stable Video Diffusion —
                    an AI that animates still images into short looping videos. Clouds drift,
                    water ripples, trees sway. The background you see isn't a photo. It's a
                    Bob Ross painting, breathing.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">🌤️</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">Painted with real weather</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    Before each painting is created, the site checks the actual weather
                    in Lehi, Utah in real time via Open-Meteo. Sunny skies, snow, thunderstorms, fog —
                    whatever the weather is outside, it gets painted into the scene.
                    The art literally reflects the world right now.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">⏱️</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">Your countdown, your timezone</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    The days, hours, minutes, and seconds shown are calculated in your
                    local timezone — not the server's. The browser sends its UTC offset
                    on first load, and the countdown clock targets midnight on August 5th
                    exactly where you are in the world.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">🖼️</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">A growing gallery</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    Every painting is permanently archived in the Gallery. You can browse
                    the entire collection, see which holidays each day celebrated, the score
                    Claude gave each painting, and who was viewing from where in the world.
                    Each day is a small piece of this journey.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">▶️</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">Timelapse player</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    Inside the Gallery, a built-in timelapse player lets you watch every
                    painting play back in sequence — from the very first day all the way to
                    today. Watch the seasons change, the holidays shift, and the journey unfold
                    painting by painting.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">🎯</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">Milestone moments</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    On special countdown numbers — 365 days, 100 days, 50, 25, 10, 5, 3, 2, 1 —
                    the site comes alive with a full-screen celebration. The closer to August 5th,
                    the more dramatic the effect. And as you approach each milestone, a quiet
                    reminder appears to keep you coming back.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">👁️</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">Live visitors from around the world</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    A live sidebar tracks who's viewing the countdown right now and where
                    they're visiting from — down to the US state level. Every view is logged
                    and visible inside each gallery entry so you can see exactly who was
                    watching on any given day.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature">
            <div class="about-feature-icon">📷</div>
            <div class="about-feature-body">
                <div class="about-feature-title">Personal memories</div>
                <div class="about-feature-desc">
                    Inside any gallery day, you can upload your own photos — memories
                    from that day. They live alongside the AI painting, turning the gallery
                    into a scrapbook of the whole journey, not just the art.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <div class="about-section-label">How it works</div>

    <div class="about-pipeline">

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">01</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Find a holiday</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    At midnight each day, the server queries a public holidays API to find
                    every holiday being celebrated somewhere in the world on that date.
                    One is selected — preference given to culturally rich, visually interesting ones.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">02</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Check the weather</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    Open-Meteo's free API is called for Lehi, Utah's current conditions.
                    Temperature, precipitation, wind speed, and weather code are translated
                    into a human-readable description — "light snow", "thunderstorm", "clear sky" —
                    and tagged with an intensity value from 0 to 1.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">03</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Claude writes the prompt</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    Claude Sonnet 4.6 receives the holiday name, country, and weather data.
                    It writes a 250–350 word image generation prompt that describes a full
                    Bob Ross oil painting scene — sky, mountains, trees, water, cultural focal
                    element, specific Bob Ross paint colors, and lighting. This prompt is
                    purpose-built to get the best result out of Flux 2 Pro.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">04</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Flux 2 Pro paints it</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    The prompt is sent to Replicate's API where black-forest-labs/flux-2-pro
                    renders a 1008×1008 PNG. Flux 2 Pro is one of the highest-quality
                    diffusion models available, capable of photorealistic painterly output
                    with precise prompt adherence. The image takes 30–90 seconds to generate.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">05</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Claude scores the result</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    The finished image is sent back to Claude Sonnet 4.6 as a vision input.
                    Claude evaluates it on four axes: painterly quality, cultural accuracy,
                    composition, and color. If the score is below 7.5 out of 10, a new attempt
                    is made with a revised prompt. Up to 3 attempts are made; the best result wins.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">06</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Stable Video Diffusion animates it</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    The winning PNG is uploaded to Replicate's file hosting, then passed to
                    stability-ai/stable-video-diffusion. SVD generates 25 frames of subtle
                    motion — clouds moving, water shimmering, light shifting — and encodes
                    them as an MP4 at 6fps. The static image is replaced by the living video
                    as soon as it's ready.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">07</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Everything is cached locally</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    The PNG, MP4, weather JSON, and art metadata are all written to disk on
                    the homelab server. The app never re-generates what it already has.
                    The Gallery reads directly from this file cache — no database needed for art.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-pipeline-step">
            <div class="about-pipeline-num">08</div>
            <div class="about-pipeline-body">
                <div class="about-pipeline-title">Viewers are tracked in SQLite</div>
                <div class="about-pipeline-desc">
                    Every page load logs an IP address, which is geolocated using ip-api.com
                    to a country and US state. These are aggregated and shown live in the sidebar
                    and stored permanently so each gallery day shows exactly who watched that day.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Tech stack deep dive -->
    <div class="about-section-label">The tech stack</div>

    <div class="about-tech-deep">

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Blazor Server (.NET 9)</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                The entire app — UI, real-time updates, background services — runs as a single
                Blazor Server application. Components communicate over a persistent SignalR
                WebSocket connection, so the countdown clock, live viewer list, and generation
                status bar all update in real time without any JavaScript framework or API layer.
                Hosted as a .NET systemd service inside a Proxmox LXC container.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic)</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                Claude is used twice per day: first to write the image generation prompt
                (text completion, temperature 0.9 for creativity), then to score the finished
                image (vision input, temperature 0 for consistent judgment). The Anthropic .NET
                SDK handles both calls. Claude's multimodal vision capability is what makes
                the iterative scoring loop possible.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Flux 2 Pro (black-forest-labs via Replicate)</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                Flux 2 Pro is a state-of-the-art text-to-image diffusion model from Black Forest Labs.
                It's called via Replicate's REST API — a prediction is submitted, polled every 3 seconds,
                and the output PNG is downloaded when complete. Flux 2 Pro was chosen over earlier
                models for its photorealism, prompt adherence, and ability to render painterly textures.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Stable Video Diffusion (Stability AI via Replicate)</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                SVD takes a single still image and generates a short video by predicting 25 frames
                of realistic motion. The PNG is first uploaded to Replicate's file hosting API to get
                a hosted URL, which is then passed as input to the model. The output is a looping MP4
                served directly from the art cache and played in a full-screen HTML5 video element.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Open-Meteo</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                Open-Meteo is a free, open-source weather API with no key required.
                It's called with Lehi, Utah's coordinates each morning to fetch current temperature,
                wind speed, precipitation, and WMO weather code. The weather code is mapped to one
                of eight visual effect types (sun, rain, snow, storm, fog, wind, heat, aurora)
                and an intensity value that controls particle count and behavior in the UI.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">SQLite (via EF Core)</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                Viewer tracking data lives in a local SQLite database. Each page view writes a row
                with IP hash, country, US state, and timestamp. Entity Framework Core handles
                migrations and queries. SQLite was chosen for simplicity — no server to manage,
                file lives on disk alongside the art cache, survives container restarts.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Proxmox + LXC</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                The app runs inside a Debian LXC container managed by Proxmox VE on a homelab server.
                LXC containers are lightweight (less overhead than a full VM), share the host kernel,
                and boot in seconds. The container gets a fixed IP on the home network and is
                managed by a systemd service that restarts the app on failure.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">Cloudflare Tunnel</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                Rather than opening ports on the home router, a Cloudflare Tunnel
                (cloudflared) runs inside the container and creates an outbound-only encrypted
                connection to Cloudflare's edge. Public traffic hits Cloudflare, gets routed
                through the tunnel to the app, and is served with full TLS — no port forwarding,
                no DDoS exposure, no dynamic DNS required.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-tech-block">
            <div class="about-tech-block-name">GitHub Actions (CI/CD)</div>
            <div class="about-tech-block-desc">
                Every push to master triggers a GitHub Actions workflow that SSH's into the
                homelab server, pulls the latest code, runs dotnet publish, copies the output
                into the container via lxc-attach, and restarts the systemd service.
                Environment variables (API keys, cache paths) are stored as GitHub Secrets
                and written into a .env file on the server at deploy time.
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Built with chips -->
    <div class="about-built">
        <div class="about-section-label">Built with</div>
        <div class="about-tech-row">
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Flux 2 Pro</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Stable Video Diffusion</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Claude Sonnet 4.6</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Blazor Server</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Replicate API</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Open-Meteo</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">SQLite + EF Core</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Proxmox LXC</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">Cloudflare Tunnel</span>
            <span class="about-tech-chip">GitHub Actions</span>
        </div>
        <p class="about-built-note">
            Running on a homelab server, painted fresh every day, counting down to one moment.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="about-footer">
        <span class="about-footer-heart">♡</span>
        <span>August 5th, 2026</span>
        <span class="about-footer-heart">♡</span>
    </div>

</div>
